-- Toyota Motor May Stop China Plant After Worker Strike, Asahi Daily Says
-- Kazuyo Sawa
-- 2010-06-16T22:25:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/toyota-may-stop-production-at-china-plant-after-worker-strike-asahi-says.html

          
          
             Toyota Motor Corp. told its
suppliers that it may be forced stop an assembly line in
Tianjin, China as early as June 17 because of a strike at a
parts factory in the same city, the Asahi newspaper said.    
 Workers at the parts plant may have been on strike since
June 15, the newspaper reported, citing an unidentified person
familiar with the situation.  
